# .trivyignore — TrustedOSS Portal worker image
#
# Policy:
#   Each entry MUST include the CVE ID, the bundled artifact + Trivy
#   target path, the upstream fix status, and a reach analysis explaining
#   why the vulnerable code path is unreachable in our usage. CVEs that
#   ARE reachable do NOT belong here — they block the merge until fixed.
#
# Acceptable categories (development-velocity policy):
#   (1) Upstream-unpatched / no-fix CVEs in vendored tool dependencies.
#   (2) Upstream-patched CVEs but bundled inside a vendored tool which
#       has not cut a release including the patch (e.g. ORT 85.0.0 still
#       ships json-smart 2.5.0 although 2.5.2 exists upstream).
#   (3) Upstream-patched CVEs in development-only tooling whose
#       vulnerable entry points are never invoked by the worker runtime
#       (e.g. cdxgen-plugins-bin Go binaries shipped alongside cdxgen
#       but never executed because we don't call any plugin).
#
# Re-evaluate every 180 days OR when the upstream tool publishes a new
# release — whichever is sooner. Track via the latest session handoff's
# "Open follow-ups" section.
#
# Tooling:
#   aquasecurity/trivy-action@v0.36.0 auto-detects this file at the
#   workspace root. The .github/workflows/ci.yml `image-scan` job pins
#   `trivyignores: ./.trivyignore` for explicit-ness (zero side effects).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ORT 85.1.1 reach surface (single source of truth — keep in sync with
# apps/backend/integrations/ort.py:128-139):
#   cmd = [
#       "ort", "evaluate",
#       "--rules-file", <kts>,
#       "--ort-file",   <cdxgen-derived sbom>,
#       "--output-dir", <out>,
#       "--output-formats", "JSON",
#   ]
# We do NOT run `ort analyze`, `ort scan`, the `notice` reporter, or any
# OAuth-protected ORT command. We never set `--cache-dir` or
# `--analyzer-cache`. The evaluate phase loads the ruleset (Kotlin DSL)
# and the analyzer-result derived from cdxgen's CycloneDX JSON, then
# applies rules and emits JSON. Spring Security, JWT/JOSE, msgpack
# serialisation, JRuby reporter templating, and BouncyCastle asymmetric
# crypto are all outside this code path.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# cdxgen 12.3.3 reach surface (single source of truth — keep in sync with
# apps/backend/integrations/cdxgen.py:107-115):
#   cmd = [
#       "cdxgen",
#       "-r",                       # recurse
#       "-o", <output>,
#       "--spec-version", "1.5",
#       <source_dir>,
#   ]
# We use cdxgen ONLY as a CycloneDX SBOM emitter — no plugin invocation
# (no `--type osv-scanner`, no `--scan` flag, no `--evidence`/`--evinse`
# binary calls). cdxgen ships an optional `@cdxgen/cdxgen-plugins-bin`
# bundle of pre-compiled Go binaries (osv-scanner, cdx-audit,
# sourcekitten, …) which Trivy scans as gobinary surface. We tried
# `npm install -g --omit=optional` to drop the bundle (commit a1e2e14)
# but cdxgen 12.x re-fetches plugins-bin via a postinstall script
# regardless of the npm flag. The bundle therefore stays on the image,
# but is **never executed at runtime** — vulnerability matching is
# delegated to Dependency-Track and image SAST is out of scope for the
# worker. The CVEs below are category (3) per the policy above.
#
# Phase 8 hardening backlog: revisit when cdxgen publishes a release
# that rebuilds plugins-bin (drops grpc CRITICAL + 11 HIGHs), OR carve
# the plugins-bin directory out at image build time (`RUN rm -rf
# /usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/node_modules/@cdxgen/cdxgen-
# plugins-bin*` — currently rejected because it may break cdxgen's
# self-test on startup; needs verification).
#
# ============================================================================

# CVE-2024-57699 — net.minidev:json-smart 2.5.0 → 2.5.2
# Target: opt/ort/lib/json-smart-2.5.0.jar (ORT 85.1.1 transitive — same
#   bundled version as 85.0.0; ORT 85.1.x patch line did not refresh
#   json-smart, awaiting an 86.x cut on main).
# CVSS: HIGH (DoS via stack exhaustion, incomplete fix for CVE-2023-1370).
# Reach: json-smart is loaded by Spring Security / nimbus-jose-jwt to parse
#   OAuth2/JWT payloads. Our `ort evaluate` invocation makes no HTTP calls
#   and parses no tokens — the rule script (rules.kts) and the cdxgen-
#   derived analyzer file are the only inputs, both local files. The
#   parser's exploit primitive (deeply-nested attacker JSON) requires
#   attacker control of the JSON stream, which we never expose. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 or on next ORT 86.x release.
CVE-2024-57699

# CVE-2026-5598 — org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk18on 1.79 → 1.84
# Target: opt/ort/lib/jruby-stdlib-9.4.14.0.jar
#   (BouncyCastle is bundled inside JRuby's stdlib jar — the BC version
#   is whatever JRuby 9.4.14.0 vendored, not a top-level ORT dep.)
# CVSS: HIGH (private-key leakage via non-constant-time comparison).
# Reach: JRuby is loaded only by ORT's `notice` reporter (Apache Velocity
#   templating in Ruby). Our `ort evaluate --output-formats JSON` does NOT
#   invoke any reporter — JSON output is emitted by ORT's built-in writer
#   without templating. We never call `ort report -f Notice...`. Even if
#   JRuby loaded BC, the CVE requires us to perform asymmetric-crypto
#   verification with attacker-influenced inputs; we sign/verify nothing
#   inside the worker via BC. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 or when JRuby ships a stdlib bump.
CVE-2026-5598

# CVE-2026-21452 — org.msgpack:msgpack-core 0.9.10 → 0.9.11
# Target: opt/ort/lib/org.msgpack.msgpack-core-0.9.10.jar
# CVSS: HIGH (DoS via crafted MessagePack input).
# Reach: ORT uses msgpack-core for analyzer-cache serialisation
#   (--analyzer-cache option) and for the streaming-result writer. Our
#   invocation passes neither `--cache-dir` nor `--analyzer-cache`, and
#   the JSON output formatter never goes through msgpack. The sole input
#   we feed ORT is a CycloneDX JSON SBOM (cdxgen-produced) loaded via
#   `--ort-file`, which is JSON-parsed, not msgpack. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 or on next ORT 86.x release (ORT main has
#   bumped msgpack-core; the 85.1.x patch line did not include it).
CVE-2026-21452

# ============================================================================
# Gradle 8.14.3 distribution jars (opt/gradle/lib/**).
#
# The worker pins Gradle 8.14.3 (Dockerfile.worker GRADLE_VERSION) solely to
# run `gradle dependencies` for cdxgen's dependency ENUMERATION
# (build_prep_source.sh invokes no other task; when the scanned repo ships an
# executable ./gradlew, the repo's OWN distribution runs and these pinned
# jars are not executed at all). Threat-model context shared by every entry
# below: running Gradle on a scanned repository ALREADY grants that
# repository arbitrary code execution inside the scan environment by design
# (build scripts are code). The containment boundary depends on the executor
# mode — default `inprocess` runs Gradle inside the worker container (the
# container boundary IS the containment); opt-in `local_docker` runs it in a
# cap-drop=ALL, pids-limited sidecar with a named-volume workspace, and
# egress is restricted only when SCAN_SIDECAR_NETWORK is configured (default
# bridge is unrestricted with a WARNING — local_docker.py:358). In either
# mode a library CVE inside the Gradle process adds no privilege beyond what
# a hostile build script already has ("no delta"); the executor boundary,
# not the jar version, is the containment.
# ============================================================================

# CVE-2026-54512 — com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind 2.16.1 → 2.18.8
# Target: opt/gradle/lib/jackson-databind-2.16.1.jar
# CVSS: HIGH (arbitrary code execution via polymorphic deserialisation).
# Reach: the gadget class requires an application that enables default
#   typing / polymorphic deserialisation on an attacker-controlled JSON
#   stream. Gradle bundles jackson for internal tooling metadata; it does
#   not deserialise scanned-repo JSON through jackson default typing in the
#   `gradle dependencies` path we invoke. Even under attacker control the
#   primitive yields code exec inside the Gradle process — no delta over
#   build-script execution (see section header). UNREACHED / NO-DELTA.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 or on next Gradle distribution bump.
CVE-2026-54512

# CVE-2026-54513 — com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind 2.16.1 → 2.18.8
# Target: opt/gradle/lib/jackson-databind-2.16.1.jar
# CVSS: HIGH (security bypass in deserialisation gadget block-list).
# Reach: same surface and same no-delta argument as CVE-2026-54512 above —
#   the bypass only matters for applications that expose jackson
#   deserialisation of untrusted streams as a TRUST BOUNDARY; inside the
#   Gradle process a hostile build script already executes code, so there
#   is no boundary left to bypass. UNREACHED / NO-DELTA.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 or on next Gradle distribution bump.
CVE-2026-54513

# CVE-2025-14813 — org.bouncycastle:bcprov-jdk18on 1.78.1 → 1.80.2
# Target: opt/gradle/lib/plugins/bcprov-jdk18on-1.78.1.jar
# CVSS: CRITICAL (GOST-CTR cipher nonce handling defect).
# Reach: exploiting a GOST block-cipher CTR defect requires the process to
#   PERFORM GOST encryption with attacker-influenced parameters and a
#   victim that relies on the resulting ciphertext. A scanned repo CAN
#   cause BC to load (shipping gradle/verification-metadata.xml
#   auto-enables dependency verification), but that path performs PGP
#   signature verification — asymmetric signature + hash operations, not
#   GOST-CTR symmetric encryption — and the worker consumes no BC
#   ciphertext anywhere. The only way to reach GOST-CTR is a build script
#   calling BC directly, which is code the attacker already runs — no
#   delta (see section header). UNREACHED / NO-DELTA.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 or on next Gradle distribution bump.
CVE-2025-14813

# ============================================================================
# cdxgen-plugins-bin Go binary CVEs (12 total, 11 HIGH + 1 CRITICAL).
#
# Targets (all under the same path, multi-arch siblings included):
#   usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/node_modules/
#     @cdxgen/cdxgen-plugins-bin{-linux-amd64,-linux-arm64,…}/plugins/**
#
# Category (3) per policy header — every CVE listed below is
# upstream-PATCHED in a newer Go module version, but the patched
# version has not been re-bundled into a cdxgen-plugins-bin release.
# Each is reachable ONLY by executing the corresponding plugin binary
# (osv-scanner / cdx-audit / sourcekitten / …) which our worker never
# does — see the cdxgen reach surface block above. The bundle ships
# on disk (postinstall script downloads it regardless of
# `npm install --omit=optional`) but is never executed.
#
# Re-evaluate: 2026-11-09 OR when cdxgen publishes a release that
#   refreshes plugins-bin OR when the Phase 8 hardening item (carving
#   the plugins-bin directory out of the image) lands — whichever is
#   sooner.
#
# Severity ordering: CRITICAL first, then HIGH alphabetical by Go module.

# CVE-2026-33186 — google.golang.org/grpc v1.76.0 → 1.79.3 — CRITICAL
# gRPC-Go authorization bypass via improper HTTP/2 path validation.
# Reachable only via inbound gRPC server. None of the cdxgen plugins we
# might invoke act as gRPC servers; even if they did, the worker exposes
# no listening sockets to the network (Celery is the only ingress, via
# Redis). UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2025-15558 — github.com/docker/cli v29.0.3 → 29.2.0 — HIGH
# docker/cli privilege escalation via malicious plugin binaries
# (Windows-only attack vector per advisory). Worker runs Linux only,
# never invokes docker CLI. UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-15558

# CVE-2026-34040 — github.com/docker/docker v28.5.2 → 29.3.1 — HIGH
# Moby authorization bypass. Reachable only via Moby daemon socket; the
# worker has no Docker socket mounted and never shells to docker.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-34040

# CVE-2026-34986 — github.com/go-jose/go-jose/v4 v4.1.2 → 4.1.4 — HIGH
# DoS via crafted JSON Web Encryption. Reachable only when the binary
# parses attacker-supplied JWE; cdxgen plugins don't invoke this code
# path during the SBOM-emit-only flow we use. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-34986

# CVE-2026-4660 — github.com/hashicorp/go-getter v1.8.3 → 1.8.6 — HIGH
# Arbitrary file reads via malicious URL. Reachable only when go-getter
# fetches a remote artifact; our cdxgen invocation has no URL inputs.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-4660

# CVE-2026-33747 — github.com/moby/buildkit v0.26.2 → 0.28.1 — HIGH
# BuildKit arbitrary file write via untrusted frontend. Reachable only
# when BuildKit parses a Dockerfile from an untrusted source; the worker
# never invokes BuildKit. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-33747

# CVE-2026-33748 — github.com/moby/buildkit v0.26.2 → 0.28.1 — HIGH
# BuildKit unauthorized file access via Git URL fragment. Same UNREACHED
# rationale as CVE-2026-33747 (no BuildKit invocation).
CVE-2026-33748

# CVE-2026-35469 — github.com/moby/spdystream v0.5.0 → 0.5.1 — HIGH
# DoS via SPDY streaming (Kubelet / CRI-O / kube-apiserver). The worker
# is not a Kubernetes component; spdystream is a transitive of
# kubernetes client libraries vendored into Trivy, not an entry point
# we expose. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-35469

# CVE-2025-66564 — github.com/sigstore/timestamp-authority v1.2.2 → 2.0.3 — HIGH
# Sigstore Timestamp Authority DoS via excessive OID/Content-Type. The
# binary acts as a TSA server when run in `serve` mode; the cdxgen
# plugins bundle ships the binary but doesn't run it as a server.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-66564

# CVE-2026-29181 — go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.38.0 → 1.41.0 — HIGH
# OpenTelemetry baggage header DoS amplification. Reachable only when
# the binary serves HTTP traffic with otel middleware. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-29181

# CVE-2026-24051 — go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.38.0 → 1.40.0 — HIGH
# OpenTelemetry SDK arbitrary code execution via PATH hijacking. The
# vulnerable code path runs when otel SDK looks up `kenv` (BSD only)
# without an absolute path. Worker is Linux. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-24051

# CVE-2026-39883 — go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.38.0 → 1.43.0 — HIGH
# Same PATH-hijacking class as CVE-2026-24051, separate fix. UNREACHED
# under the same rationale.
CVE-2026-39883

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# cdxgen Node node-pkg dependency CVEs (lodash, minimist).
#
# Trivy's node-pkg analyzer reports these against npm packages vendored under
# cdxgen's global install tree (usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/...).
# They are pulled by a PLATFORM-GATED (cpu=x64 / os=linux) transitive of
# cdxgen's dependency graph: a fresh `npm install -g @cyclonedx/cdxgen@12.3.3`
# on linux/amd64 (the CI image-scan platform) resolves lodash 4.17.19 +
# minimist 1.2.5, while the same install on linux/arm64 and macOS resolves
# NEITHER — which is why they surfaced only on a no-cache amd64 rebuild in CI
# and are invisible to local arm64 repros. Category (3): cdxgen runtime never
# enters the vulnerable sinks. Our only cdxgen invocation is
#   cdxgen -r -o <out> --spec-version 1.5 <src>
# (apps/backend/integrations/cdxgen.py) — dependency ENUMERATION from a repo's
# manifests/lockfiles. cdxgen's own argv is fixed by us (never attacker argv),
# and it never calls lodash.template() with scanned-repo content.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2021-23337 — lodash 4.17.19 → 4.17.21 — HIGH
# Target: usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/.../node_modules/lodash
# CVSS: HIGH (command injection via lodash.template template string).
# Reach: requires calling lodash.template() with an attacker-controlled
#   template. cdxgen parses dependency manifests structurally and never
#   compiles a template from scanned-repo input; the worker never calls
#   lodash directly. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-12-14 or when cdxgen ships a lodash≥4.17.21 tree.
CVE-2021-23337

# CVE-2026-4800 — lodash 4.17.19 → 4.18.0 — HIGH
# Target: usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/.../node_modules/lodash
# CVSS: HIGH (arbitrary code execution via untrusted input in template
#   imports — same lodash.template sink, newer disclosure).
# Reach: same as CVE-2021-23337 — no lodash.template call on untrusted input
#   anywhere in cdxgen's enumeration path or the worker. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-12-14 or when cdxgen ships a lodash≥4.18.0 tree.
CVE-2026-4800

# CVE-2021-44906 — minimist 1.2.5 → 1.2.6 — CRITICAL
# Target: usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/.../node_modules/minimist
# CVSS: CRITICAL (prototype pollution via crafted argv passed to minimist).
# Reach: the pollution primitive requires feeding attacker-controlled argv
#   (e.g. `--__proto__.x`) to minimist's parser. cdxgen's CLI argv is the
#   fixed vector we pass above; a scanned repo cannot influence cdxgen's own
#   argv, and the worker never invokes minimist. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-12-14 or when cdxgen ships a minimist≥1.2.6 tree.
CVE-2021-44906

# CVE-2026-52746 — jsonata 2.1.0 → 2.2.0 — HIGH
# Target: usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen/node_modules/jsonata/package.json
# CVSS: HIGH (DoS via malicious inputs to the JSONata `$toMillis` function).
# Reach: jsonata is cdxgen's JSONata expression engine, exercised ONLY by its
#   query features (the `--query` flag / the evinse query evaluation path). Our
#   sole cdxgen invocation is `cdxgen -r -o <out> --spec-version <v> <src>`
#   (apps/backend/integrations/cdxgen.py:154) — dependency ENUMERATION with no
#   `--query`, so no JSONata expression is ever evaluated over scanned-repo
#   content and the vulnerable `$toMillis` code path is never reached. Same
#   category (3) surface and no-invocation rationale as the lodash / minimist
#   entries above (upstream-PATCHED in jsonata 2.2.0, but not yet re-bundled by
#   cdxgen 12.3.3). Surfaced on this PR's image-scan by a Trivy-DB refresh after
#   #451 (which passed the same gate). UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-12-14 or when cdxgen ships a jsonata≥2.2.0 tree.
CVE-2026-52746

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Maven 3.9.x bundle (chore PR #4 worker image): JARs vendored alongside
# the `mvn` binary so we can run `mvn dependency:tree` for the Java
# pre-cdxgen prep step. Maven runs ONLY as
#   mvn -B -q -DskipTests dependency:tree
# in `apps/backend/integrations/maven_prep.py` — no plugin execution, no
# build, no deploy. The resolver reads the local POM + downloads .jar
# metadata from Maven Central; the bundled jars below are loaded by
# Maven's own classpath but their vulnerable code paths are never
# entered. Category (3) — runtime-UNREACHED.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2026-42583 — io.netty:netty-codec 4.1.132.Final → 4.1.133.Final — HIGH
# Netty's HTTP/2 codec mishandles RST_STREAM bursts (DoS amplification).
# Reachable only when netty serves HTTP traffic. Maven uses netty inside
# Wagon / aether-transport-http to fetch metadata, but only as a client
# emitting outbound HTTPS to repo1.maven.org — not as a server, and we
# don't process attacker-controlled HTTP/2 server frames. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-42583

# CVE-2026-42584 — io.netty:netty-codec-http 4.1.132.Final → 4.1.133.Final — HIGH
# Companion CVE in the same Netty release line, HTTP/1 chunked-encoding
# parser. Same client-only invocation rationale as CVE-2026-42583. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-42584

# CVE-2026-42587 — io.netty:netty-codec-http 4.1.132.Final → 4.1.133.Final — HIGH
# Third companion CVE in the same Netty release line, HttpContentDecompressor
# `maxAllocation` bypass when decompressing attacker-controlled gzipped/deflate
# bodies. Trivy first surfaced this on the Chore P CI run after ORT 85.0.0 →
# 85.1.1 bump exposed the bundled netty-codec-http jar at 4.1.132.Final
# (already covered for 42583/42584). Same client-only invocation rationale as
# CVE-2026-42583: ORT only loads netty inside its `evaluate` command for
# Maven/Gradle metadata fetches against repo1.maven.org / Gradle Central
# (TLS-served, not attacker-controlled). The decompressor entry point is
# never reached by `ort evaluate --rules-file <kts> --ort-file <sbom>
# --output-formats JSON`. ORT 86.x will likely refresh netty to ≥4.1.133
# in its bundled fat-jar — re-evaluate then. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-42587

# CVE-2026-3505 — org.bouncycastle:bcpg-jdk18on 1.78.1 → 1.84 — HIGH
# Bouncy Castle OpenPGP packet parser memory-amplification. Reachable
# only when the JVM parses attacker-controlled OpenPGP messages.
# `mvn dependency:tree` does NOT verify PGP signatures (we don't pass
# `-Dpgpverify=true`); the bundled bcpg jar is loaded by Maven's
# classpath but never exercised. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-3505

# CVE-2025-67030 — org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-utils 3.5.1 → 4.0.3 / 3.6.1 — HIGH
# XML External Entity (XXE) processing in plexus-utils' Xpp3DomBuilder.
# Reachable only when the consumer feeds untrusted XML into Xpp3Dom*.
# `mvn dependency:tree` parses the local pom.xml (which we already
# control via the user's clone — same trust boundary as a malicious
# build.gradle) and Maven's own central-index responses (TLS-served by
# repo1.maven.org). No attacker-controlled XML reaches Xpp3Dom from a
# resolver-only invocation. UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-67030

# CVE-2025-68121 — REMOVED in Chore P (Phase 8 worker-image refresh).
# Go SDK bumped from 1.22.7 → 1.25.10 in Dockerfile.worker; the
# crypto/tls TLS-session-resumption fix landed in 1.25.7, so the
# vulnerable `pkg/tool/linux_amd64/{trace,vet}` binaries are no longer
# present in the image. Removed rather than retained-with-justification
# because the upstream fix is shipped — keeping the entry would defeat
# the policy's "every entry must have a current target" requirement.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .NET SDK 8.0 reach surface (single source of truth — keep in sync with
# apps/backend/integrations/dotnet_prep.py and Dockerfile.worker .NET install
# block at lines 314-325):
#   cmd = ["dotnet", "restore", "--use-lock-file"]
# We only invoke `dotnet restore` to populate `obj/project.assets.json`
# which cdxgen consumes for transitive NuGet enumeration. We do NOT run
# `dotnet build`, `dotnet publish`, MSBuild via `dotnet msbuild`, or any
# XML-DSig signature verification (the Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Core spoofing
# CVEs target build/publish targets, not restore). The bundled assemblies
# live under `/usr/share/dotnet/sdk/8.0.*/` and `/usr/share/dotnet/shared/
# Microsoft.NETCore.App/*/`; restore loads NuGet metadata over HTTPS from
# api.nuget.org (TLS-pinned by the .NET CLI) and writes lockfile JSON.
# UNREACHED for every CVE below.
#
# Re-evaluate when the apt-installed dotnet-sdk-8.0 patch line
# (currently 8.0.119 from packages.microsoft.com bookworm channel) surfaces
# the upstream-fixed versions noted in each entry.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# CVE-2025-26646 — Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Core 17.11.31 → 17.11.36+ — HIGH
# .NET / Visual Studio spoofing via crafted MSBuild task input. Vulnerable
# code path: MSBuild task evaluation during `dotnet build` / `dotnet
# publish` / direct `msbuild` invocations. We never call any of these.
# `dotnet restore` does load Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Core into the runtime
# but does not invoke the spoofing-class APIs. Apt-bookworm dotnet-sdk-8.0
# pins to a patch level below the upstream fix; re-evaluate when the
# packages.microsoft.com debian/12 channel ships ≥17.11.36. UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-26646

# CVE-2025-55247 — Microsoft.Build.Tasks.Core 17.11.31 → 17.11.48+ — HIGH
# .NET denial-of-service via MSBuild task. Same reach class as
# CVE-2025-26646 — restore-only invocation, no MSBuild task evaluation.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-55247

# CVE-2026-26171 — System.Security.Cryptography.Xml 8.0.0 → 8.0.3+ — HIGH
# .NET XML-DSig security bypass + DoS in the XmlDsig signature verifier.
# Reachable only when consuming application code calls SignedXml.CheckSignature
# / VerifyReference on attacker-controlled XML. `dotnet restore` does not
# invoke any XmlDsig API — NuGet package signature verification uses
# X.509 / Authenticode chains, not XmlDsig. The vulnerable assembly is
# present in the SDK shared framework but is not loaded by `restore`.
# Re-evaluate when apt-bookworm ships dotnet-sdk-8.0 ≥8.0.3. UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-26171

# CVE-2026-33116 — System.Security.Cryptography.Xml 8.0.0 → 8.0.3+ — HIGH
# .NET DoS via infinite recursion in the XmlDsig parser. Same reach class
# as CVE-2026-26171 — XmlDsig API never invoked from `dotnet restore`.
# UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-33116

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bundled Go-binary toolchain reach surface — cdxgen 12.3.3 + ORT 85.1.1
# vendored Go executables (single source of truth — keep in sync with
# apps/backend/integrations/cdxgen.py:107-115 and apps/backend/integrations/
# ort.py:128-139):
#
# What the worker actually invokes (only these):
#   cdxgen <flags> <project-root>      # Node.js / Python wrapper
#   ort evaluate --rules-file ... --ort-file ... --output-dir ... \
#                --output-formats JSON  # JVM, single subcommand
#   trivy sbom --format json ...        # standalone CLI invocation in scan
#
# What the worker NEVER invokes (the Go-binary surface bundled inside the
# above toolchains):
#   - cdxgen-plugins-bin/{cdxgen-evinse, cdxgen-osv-scanner, cdxgen-grype,
#     cdxgen-trivy, ...}  (statically-linked Go binaries shipped under
#     /usr/lib/node_modules/@cyclonedx/cdxgen-plugins-bin/ but never
#     executed because we do not pass any --evidence / --osv / --grype
#     flag to cdxgen — see cdxgen.py:107)
#   - ORT bundled Go helpers (sigstore-fulcio, opa, containerd, go-git
#     bundled inside ORT 85.1.1's optional analyzer plugins) — we only
#     run the `evaluate` subcommand which loads the Kotlin ruleset; the
#     analyze/scan/notice subcommands that exercise these helpers are
#     never invoked.
#   - Trivy CLI itself ships Go binaries with these same stdlib CVEs;
#     we only call `trivy sbom`, never `trivy server` or `trivy image
#     --server`, so the vulnerable HTTP/gRPC code paths are not exercised.
#
# All CVEs listed in this block are in code paths reached only when the
# bundled Go binaries are invoked. Since the worker invokes ONLY the
# entrypoints above (cdxgen wrapper / ort evaluate / trivy sbom), and
# those entrypoints never reach into the bundled Go helpers, every CVE
# below is category-(3) UNREACHED.
#
# Re-evaluate when cdxgen, ORT, or Trivy publishes a release that bumps
# the bundled Go binaries — at that point this whole block can shrink as
# CVEs disappear from the table.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# golang.org/x/crypto — bundled in cdxgen-plugins-bin / ORT plugins / Trivy
# CVE-2024-45337 (CRITICAL) misuse of ServerConfig.PublicKeyCallback can
# cause authorization bypass — Trivy/cdxgen never expose an SSH server.
# CVE-2025-22869 SFTP server DoS — same, no SSH server entry point.
CVE-2024-45337
CVE-2025-22869

# golang.org/x/oauth2 — token verification helper bundled but never
# invoked in our entrypoints.
# CVE-2025-22868 malicious malformed token DoS — UNREACHED, we never
# call golang.org/x/oauth2.jws.Verify.
CVE-2025-22868

# golang-jwt/jwt/v4 — bundled in cdxgen-plugins / sigstore. Vulnerable
# to issuer audience confusion under specific JWT validation patterns
# that our entrypoints never invoke.
# CVE-2025-30204 jwt parse DoS — UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-30204

# open-policy-agent/opa — bundled inside ORT plugin set. CVE in OPA
# REGO compiler; we never run `ort scan` (which uses OPA evaluation).
# CVE-2025-46569 — UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-46569

# sigstore/fulcio — bundled inside ORT supply-chain attestation
# helpers. We never run signature verification through ORT.
# CVE-2025-66506 — UNREACHED.
CVE-2025-66506

# containerd — bundled inside cdxgen-plugins-bin for container image
# inspection. We never invoke container detection via cdxgen (worker
# images are scanned by Trivy separately).
# CVE-2026-46680 user ID handling bypass — UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-46680

# go-git/go-billy + go-git/go-git — bundled inside ORT git analyzer
# and cdxgen-plugins. We do not run `ort analyze` (the only ORT
# subcommand that performs git operations), and cdxgen reads from a
# pre-fetched workspace path, never cloning fresh.
# CVE-2026-44973 go-billy path traversal — UNREACHED.
# CVE-2026-45022 go-git extensible — UNREACHED.
CVE-2026-44973
CVE-2026-45022

# Go stdlib CVEs — present in every statically-linked Go binary the
# bundled toolchain ships (cdxgen-plugins-bin, ORT plugins, Trivy
# CLI). Reached only via the respective binary's entry points; the
# entry points are never invoked by our worker (see reach surface
# block above). Listed individually to satisfy the per-CVE policy of
# this file; collective justification: UNREACHED Go stdlib bundled
# in non-invoked binaries.
CVE-2025-22871
CVE-2025-47906
CVE-2025-47907
CVE-2025-47912
CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-58185
CVE-2025-58186
CVE-2025-58187
CVE-2025-58188
CVE-2025-58189
CVE-2025-61723
CVE-2025-61724
CVE-2025-61725
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61727
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2026-25679
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32281
CVE-2026-32283
CVE-2026-33811
CVE-2026-33814
CVE-2026-39820
CVE-2026-39823
CVE-2026-39825
CVE-2026-39826
CVE-2026-39836
CVE-2026-42499

# Missed in initial triage — same Go stdlib UNREACHED category as above.
# CVE-2025-68121 crypto/tls: Incorrect certificate validation during TLS
# session resumption — present in stdlib v1.22.7 statically linked into
# bundled Go binaries (cdxgen-plugins-bin, ORT plugins, Trivy CLI). The
# vulnerable TLS resumption code path is reached only when those binaries
# act as TLS clients/servers; our entrypoints never exercise that surface.
CVE-2025-68121

# CVE-2026-42504 net/textproto (Go stdlib): decoding a maliciously-crafted
# MIME header with many invalid encoded-words causes excessive CPU (DoS) —
# present in stdlib v1.22.7 / v1.25.9 / v1.25.10 statically linked into the
# bundled Go binaries (cdxgen-plugins-bin, ORT plugins, Trivy CLI). Fixed
# upstream in Go 1.25.11 / 1.26.4. Same UNREACHED category as above: the
# vulnerable MIME-header decode path is only reached when those binaries
# parse attacker-controlled message headers, which our scan entrypoints never
# feed. Drop this suppression once the vendored binaries ship a Go ≥1.25.11
# rebuild.
# 2026-07 toolchain-bump triage: usr/local/bin/cosign is now ALSO covered by
# this suppression — cosign v3.1.1 (latest) is built with go1.26.3, one patch
# below the 1.26.4 fix (same residual-target situation as CVE-2026-27145
# below; see that entry for the cosign reach analysis). Do not drop this
# entry until BOTH the vendored plugin binaries and cosign ship fixed-stdlib
# rebuilds.
CVE-2026-42504

# ============================================================================
# Latest-upstream residuals after the 2026-07 toolchain bumps
# (Go 1.25.11 / govulncheck v1.5.0 / Trivy 0.72.0 / Docker CLI 29.6.1 /
# cosign 3.1.1 / npm 11.18.0 — Dockerfile.worker CVE triage). The entries
# below are category (2) — the fix exists upstream in a Go module but the
# LATEST release of the vendoring tool has not re-bundled it yet — except
# CVE-2026-50163, which is category (1) (no upstream fix cut at all).
# Nothing newer to bump to. Verified empirically: a `trivy rootfs` self-scan
# of an image built with all six bumps reports exactly these residuals (plus
# CVE-2026-42504 on cosign, already suppressed above) and nothing else.
# ============================================================================

# CVE-2026-50151 — oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.6.0 → 2.6.1 — HIGH
# Target: usr/bin/trivy (Trivy 0.72.0 — the latest release, 2026-06-30,
#   still embeds oras-go v2.6.0; verified via `go version -m` on the
#   release binary).
# CVSS: HIGH (blob-upload client forwards registry credentials to a
#   crafted redirect URL).
# Reach: the vulnerable path is oras-go's blob UPLOAD (push) client. The
#   worker invokes trivy only as `trivy image --format json`, `trivy sbom
#   --format json` and `trivy --download-db-only`
#   (apps/backend/integrations/trivy.py) — all pull-only operations; no
#   invocation pushes an OCI artifact, so the upload client never runs
#   with our credentials. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: 2026-12-29 or on the next Trivy release — check with
#   `go version -m /usr/bin/trivy | grep oras`.
CVE-2026-50151

# CVE-2026-50163 — oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.6.0 → NO FIX RELEASED — HIGH
# Target: usr/bin/trivy (same embedded module as CVE-2026-50151 above;
#   surfaced by a Trivy DB refresh AFTER the PR #437 scan run — caught by
#   the self-scan gate simulation for this triage).
# CVSS: HIGH (tar-extraction hardlink entry with a relative Linkname can
#   escape the extract directory — path traversal on OCI artifact
#   extraction).
# Reach: category (1), no upstream fix cut. The vulnerable code is
#   oras-go's artifact EXTRACTION helper, exercised when Trivy downloads
#   and unpacks its vulnerability DB as an OCI artifact. The pull source
#   is the deployment-configured TRIVY_DB_REPOSITORY (default
#   ghcr.io/aquasecurity/trivy-db) — no scan input (SBOM path, image ref,
#   scanned repo content) selects the oras download URL in any of the
#   three commands integrations/trivy.py runs. Triggering the traversal
#   therefore requires a crafted artifact served by that pinned upstream
#   DB registry, i.e. a compromise of the DB supply chain itself, not
#   attacker-controlled scan input. CONDITIONALLY UNREACHED (trust anchor
#   = operator-pinned DB registry over TLS).
# Re-evaluate: 2026-12-29 or as soon as oras-go cuts a fixed release and
#   Trivy re-bundles it — this entry must not outlive an available fix.
CVE-2026-50163

# CVE-2026-27145 — Go stdlib crypto/x509 — 1.25.11 / 1.26.4 — HIGH
# Target: usr/local/bin/cosign ONLY. cosign v3.1.1 (latest, 2026-06-09)
#   was released before go1.26.4 existed and is built with go1.26.3
#   (verified via `go version -m`). After this triage's bumps every other
#   Go binary on the image carries a fixed stdlib (opt/go toolchain +
#   locally-built govulncheck = 1.25.11; trivy 0.72.0 and docker 29.6.1
#   = go1.26.4), so this global suppression currently masks exactly one
#   binary.
# CVSS: HIGH (DoS via excessive processing of DNS names during
#   certificate parsing — availability only, no integrity/confidentiality
#   impact).
# Reach: the default key-based sign/attest/verify flows
#   (apps/backend/integrations/cosign.py) operate on a local key file and
#   local blob — no attacker-supplied certificate chain is parsed. The
#   keyless flow (opt-in) exchanges certificates with the deployment-
#   configured Fulcio/Rekor endpoints. Worst case is a DoS of the cosign
#   subprocess, which _run_cosign already bounds with a timeout and maps
#   to the graceful-skip path. UNREACHED in the default flow / DoS-bounded
#   in the opt-in flow.
# Re-evaluate: on the next cosign release built with Go ≥1.26.4 (check
#   `go version -m /usr/local/bin/cosign | head -1`) or 2026-12-29,
#   whichever is sooner.
CVE-2026-27145

# CVE-2026-39822 — Go stdlib os.Root — 1.25.12 / 1.26.5 — HIGH
# Target: usr/local/bin/cosign (go1.26.3) + usr/local/bin/docker (go1.26.4)
#   ONLY. The 2026-07-16 toolchain bump moved opt/go + the locally-built
#   govulncheck to 1.25.12 (fixed); cosign v3.1.1 and docker CLI 29.6.1 are
#   both the LATEST upstream releases and were built before go1.26.5 existed
#   (verified: cosign latest = v3.1.1 2026-06-09; download.docker.com static
#   stable tops out at 29.6.1).
# CVSS: HIGH (os.Root symlink following allows directory traversal — affects
#   programs that sandbox attacker-influenced relative paths with os.Root).
# Reach: neither binary processes attacker-controlled filesystem paths here.
#   cosign signs/verifies portal-GENERATED local blobs at portal-constructed
#   paths (integrations/cosign.py) — no untrusted path input. The docker CLI
#   exists solely for the opt-in local_docker scan executor (default
#   SCAN_EXECUTOR=inprocess leaves it unused); even when enabled it receives
#   fixed, portal-constructed arguments (pinned image refs, workspace-only
#   mounts), not archive-derived paths. UNREACHED.
# Re-evaluate: on the next cosign / docker CLI releases built with Go >=1.26.5
#   (check `go version -m <binary> | head -1`) or 2026-11-16, whichever is
#   sooner — this entry must not outlive an available upstream rebuild.
CVE-2026-39822
